ss environments, preferably with exposure to real estate technology systems.\\n\\n## Development\\n### Education\\nBachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related field; equivalent practical experience may be considered.\\n\\n### Licensing and Certifications\\n- AWS Certified Solutions Architect Associate\\n- Microsoft Azure Administrator Associate (AZ-104)\\n- Google Cloud Associate Cloud Engineer\\n- HashiCorp Certified: Terraform Associate\\n- Certified Kubernetes Administrator (CKA)\\n\\n## Skills\\n### Technical Skills\\nPossesses intermediate technical proficiency to implement and manage cloud resources for real estate applications.\\n- Comprehensive Cloud Platform Implementation (AWS VPC, ECS, Lambda, Azure App Service, AKS, GCP GKE, Cloud Functions)\\n- Proficient Infrastructure as Code implementation (Terraform, CloudFormation, ARM templates)\\n- Intermediate scripting in Python and Bash for automation and deployment pipelines\\n- Implementation of cloud networking solutions including VPNs, load balancers, and security groups\\n- Application of cloud security best practices, including IAM, encryption, and compliance frameworks relevant to real estate data\\n- Design and implementation of scalable architectures for property management systems and real estate applications\\n- CI/CD pipeline configuration and maintenance\\n- Database management in cloud environments (RDS, Cosmos DB, Cloud SQL)\\n\\n### Soft Skills\\nCommunicates effectively with team members and stakeholders while managing multiple priorities.\\n- Effective technical communication with non-technical stakeholders\\n- Project organization and prioritization\\n- Requirements gathering and analysis\\n- Technical documentation creation\\n- Collaborative problem-solving\\n- Adaptability to changing requirements\\n- Customer service orientation for internal clients\\n\\n### Leadership Skills\\nDemonstrates technical leadership within defined project scope.\\n- Mentoring juni