ions, and ensuring cloud platforms effectively support business goals while optimizing costs and maintaining security for sensitive real estate data and applications.\\n\\n## Experience\\n8+ years of experience in cloud engineering and architecture with at least 3 years in a leadership role, demonstrating a track record of successfully leading cloud transformation initiatives, preferably in real estate or related industries.\\n\\n## Development\\n### Education\\nBachelor's degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or related field; Master's degree in Computer Science or MBA beneficial.\\n\\n### Licensing and Certifications\\n- AWS Certified Solutions Architect Professional\\n- AWS Certified DevOps Engineer Professional\\n- Microsoft Azure Solutions Architect Expert (AZ-305)\\n- Google Cloud Professional Cloud Architect\\n- TOGAF Certification\\n- Certified Information Security Manager (CISM)\\n- Project Management Professional (PMP)\\n- Certified Scrum Master (CSM)\\n\\n## Skills\\n### Technical Skills\\nProvides enterprise-level technical vision and leadership for cloud architecture supporting real estate business operations.\\n- Strategic Cloud Platform Direction (multi-cloud strategy, vendor evaluation, enterprise architecture)\\n- Enterprise Infrastructure as Code governance (organization-wide standards, modules, and practices)\\n- Technology evaluation and adoption strategies for real estate applications\\n- Enterprise networking architecture and global connectivity strategies\\n- Security and compliance framework development for real estate data protection\\n- Enterprise architecture patterns and reference architectures for real estate platforms\\n- Disaster recovery and business continuity planning\\n- Cloud financial operations (FinOps) and optimization strategies\\n- Data governance and management architecture for property and market data\\n\\n### Soft Skills\\nLeads through influence and communicates vision effectively across organizational level