ce this information isn't in the provided context, I'm sharing this from my general knowledge rather than the specific sources provided.\\n\\nWould you like me to elaborate more on what I know about their research in cognitive engineering and human factors?", "model": "pluto", "modelName": "PLUTO", "modelIdx": 0, "timestamp": 1768340152, "statusHistory": [{"action": "knowledge_search", "query": "What is the research by Rasmussan and Vicente that you align with?", "done": false}, {"action": "queries_generated", "queries": ["Rasmussen and Vicente cognitive systems engineering", "Abstraction hierarchies in human factors research", "Jens Rasmussen and Kim Vicente research on human-centered systems"], "done": false}, {"action": "sources_retrieved", "count": 2, "done": true}, {"action": "knowledge_search", "query": "What is the research by Rasmussan and Vicente that you align with?", "done": true, "hidden": true}], "sources": [{"source": {"id": "adbeade6-cb53-42c9-88cc-adf0f39ec6df", "user_id": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "name": "Justin's Knowledge", "description": "This is information about Justin, and relevant research.", "meta": null, "access_control": {"read": {"group_ids": [], "user_ids": []}, "write": {"group_ids": [], "user_ids": []}}, "created_at": 1768337776, "updated_at": 1768337788, "user": {"id": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "name": "Pluto System", "role": "admin", "email": "system@pluto.local"}, "write_access": true, "type": "collection"}, "document": ["Comparing cognitive tasks in complex systems is different than comparing tasks in user interface design. In cognitive engineering and human factors, a popular technique is Hierarchal Task Analysis (HTA) (see Shepherd, 1998) and deals with the decomposition and analysis of tasks. More specifically, HTA is a goal oriented framework and allows for the modelling of the cognitive and physical processes associated with achieving a system goal by breaking down the processes into sub-goals. As 