g-idol.pdf", "access_control": null}, "id": "e144d21f-1c37-490c-866d-030fdb7ca5ff", "url": "e144d21f-1c37-490c-866d-030fdb7ca5ff", "name": "dyson-logos-challenge-of-the-frog-idol.pdf", "status": "uploaded", "size": 4832584, "error": "", "itemId": "39f4a562-c12e-442d-b7b9-df0814f7cd49"}, "document": ["Challenge of the Frog Idol  \\n1. Coruvon, the Swamp Arena\\n2. Idol of the Frog God\\n3. Troglodyte Village\\n4. The Hill\\n5. The Zombie Float\\n6. The Alabaster Cave\\n7. The Nixie Pool\\n8. Labyrinth of the Rains\\n9. Heart of the Fruum\\n10. Fortress on the Ironflow\\n11. Barracks at Kuln\\n12. MirePort\\nthe Black Mire and Surrounding Regions\\n3  \\n6  \\n9\\n0  \\n1 hex = 6 miles", "9Challenge of the Frog Idol\\nThe Black Mire\\nThe Black Mire is a magical swamp dating to the ages-old war between\\nthe elven Kale and the rebellious humans. To attract the attention and\\naid of gods in their war against the Kale, the swamp was created by\\nopening a gate to a dimension of dark waters deep in the earth beneath\\nthe location of the current swamp.\\nAs the land liquefied, several alien gods from other realms arrived to\\nstake their claim here. Most are now dead, the rest forgotten. Only\\nthree have any real presence remaining - the Frog God, Plures God of\\nRains, and the Fruum. The Frog God and Plures exist within the Black\\nMire as statues, hardly able to exert their will in any noticeable way\\neven within the immediate vicinity of their idols. The Fruum, however,\\nwas a malevolent entity and survives to this day in the depths of the\\nswamp and remains jealous of the other two gods in his domain.\\nThe Black Mire is criss-crossed with ancient wooden causeways and", "3Challenge of the Frog Idol\\nRumours of Coruvon\\n1. [T] Coruvon is known as the Swamp Arena - the only entertainment\\nin town is the great arena.\\n2. [T] Traders and merchants have been leaving Coruvon for better op-\\nportunities elsewhere.\\n3. [T] The prostitutes have taken over as a major power block in town,\\nnegotiating directly with the commander of the garrison.\\n4. [T] The city has a heavy military presence, garrisons against poten -\\ntial attacks from the Giants.\\n5. [F] The oracle of Coruvon is an evil hag who lures unsuspecting ad -\\nventurers to their demise in the Black Mire\\n6. [T] Coruvon's commander of the watch has been stuck here for years\\n- probably punishment for some indiscretion in his past.\\n7. [T] The hill Coruvon was built on was once the burial mound of a clan\\nof giants.\\n8. [T] Coruvon has an oracle who can be consulted for large sums of\\ngold, however she occasionally grants free advice to those who do\\nnot seek her out."], "metadata": [{"producer": "Adobe PDF Library 7.0", "creator": "Adobe InDesign CS2 (4.0)", "creationdate": "2011-06-10T11:24:01-04:00", "moddate": "2011-06-10T11:24:19-04:00", "trapped": "/False", "source": "dyson-logos-challenge-of-the-frog-idol.pdf", "total_pages": 23, "page": 7, "page_label": "8", "name": "dyson-logos-challenge-of-the-frog-idol.pdf", "created_by": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "file_id": "e144d21f-1c37-490c-866d-030fdb7ca5ff", "start_index": 0, "hash": "c211a00a07e709a943cc2ffdf530486bb80e2a55a60aaea6370b382770c0056d", "embedding_config": {"engine": "ollama", "model": "nomic-embed-text"}}, {"producer": "Adobe PDF Library 7.0", "creator": "Adobe InDesign CS2 (4.0)", "creationdate": "2011-06-10T11:24:01-04:00", "moddate": "2011-06-10T11:24:19-04:00", "trapped": "/False", "source": "dyson-logos-challenge-of-the-frog-idol.pdf", "total_pages": 23, "page": 8, "page_label": "9", "name": "dyson-logos-challenge-of-the-frog-idol.pdf", "created_by": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "file_id": "e144d21f-1c37-490c-866d-030fdb7ca5ff", "start_index": 0, "hash": "c211a00a07e709a943cc2ffdf530486bb80e2a55a60aaea6370b382770c0056d", "embedding_config": {"engine": "ollama", "model": "nomic-embed-text"}}, {"producer": "Adobe PDF Library 7.0", "creator": "Adobe InDesign CS2 (4.0)", "creationdate": "2011-06-10T11:24:01-04:00", "moddate": "2011-06-10T11:24:19-04:00", "trapped": "/False", "source": "dyson-logos-challenge-of-the-frog-idol.pdf", "total_pages": 23, "page": 2, "page_label": "3", "name": "dyson-logos-challenge-of-the-frog-idol.pdf", "created_by": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "file_id": "e144d21f-1c37-490c-866d-030fdb7ca5ff", "start_index": 0, "hash": "c211a00a07e709a943cc2ffdf530486bb80e2a55a60aaea6370b382770c0056d", "embedding_config": {"engine": "ollama", "model": "nomic-embed-text"}}], "distances": [0.8245154, 0.81604895, 0.8050534]}], "lastSentence": "[2] Let me know if you have any other questions, Grom!", "usage": {"completion_tokens": 415, "prompt_tokens": 1706, "total_tokens": 2121, "completion_tokens_details": {"reasoning_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"cached_tokens": 0, "cache_creation_tokens": 0}, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 0}, "done": true, "followUps": ["What are the specific abilities or powers of the Frog Idol that I'm trying to help?", "Are there any important NPCs or locations in the town of Coruvon that I should seek out?", "What kinds of challenges or dangers can I expect to face while traveling through the Black Mire swamp?", "Are there any special rules or mechanics I should be aware of when dealing with the Zombie Float island?", "Can you provide more details on how to consult the oracle in Coruvon and what kind of information they might be able to provide?"]}, "d7047817-a760-453a-9267-ce30549e21f3": {"id": "d7047817-a760-453a-9267-ce30549e21f3", "parentId": "c6dad4d6-5cd6-4466-a252-9ce08c35ea64", "childrenIds": ["b3ee16a7-896f-40c9-9a87-abf38c5c1f6c"], "role": "user", "content": "What are the specific abilities or powers of the Frog Idol that I'm trying to help?", "models": ["rpg-demo---challenge-of-the-frog-idol"], "timestamp": 1768352283}, "b3ee16a7-896f-40c9-9a87-abf38c5c1f6c": {"parentId": "d7047817-a760-453a-9267-ce30549e21f3", "id": "b3ee16a7-896f-40c9-9a87-abf38c5c1f6c", "childrenIds": [], "role": "assistant", "content": "According to the context provided, the Frog Idol has the following abilities and powers that you are trying to help it recover:\\n\\n1. The Frog Idol was once wed to a beautiful woman, and it seeks the treasures of their engagement - an iron rose and a basket of amber. [2]\\n\\n2. If the party can recover these three items (the iron rose, amber basket, and four massive chunks of amber), the Frog Idol will grant them another item in trade - a stone amulet in the shape of the Frog Idol. [2]\\n\\n3. The stone amulet granted by the Frog Idol will allow the wearer to create an invisibility effect with a 10-foot radius, which is only effective against ogres and giants within the citadel of Kuln and the immediate vicinity. [2]\\n\\nSo in summary, the Frog Idol's main powers are tied to the recovery of these three specific artifacts, which will then grant the party a powerful stone amulet to aid them in fighting giants in Kuln. Let me know if you need any clarification on these abilities!", "model": "rpg-demo---challenge-of-the-frog-idol", "modelName": "RPG Demo - Challenge of the Frog Idol", "modelIdx": 0, "timestamp": 1768352283, "statusHistory": [{"action": "knowledge_search", "query": "What are the specific abilities or powers of the Frog Idol that I'm trying to help?", "done": false}, {"action": "queries_generated", "queries": ["abilities and powers of frog idol black mire", "what does the frog idol in the black mire do", "frog idol powers and functions black mire"], "done": false}, {"action": "sources_retrieved", "count": 1, "done": true}, {"action": "knowledge_search", "query": "What are the specific abilities or powers of the Frog Idol that I'm trying to help?", "done": true, "hidden": true}], "sources": [{"source": {"name": "rpg_tools/consult_oracle"}, "document": ["The Oracle speaks..."], "metadata": [{"source": "rpg_tools/consult_oracle", "parameters": {}}], "tool_result": true}, {"sourc