 enter the swamp proper is often a death\\nsentence to unwary adventurers.\\n8. [T] Years ago a sorcerer was lost in the Mire and now rules a small\\nisland of zombies.", "3Challenge of the Frog Idol\\nCurrently there are three cages with living trog females in them. One\\nof them appears even more human than the typical trog female from\\nthe village (she just has a higher charisma than her fellows). Pregnant\\ntrogs are left here in the cages for three days and then brought back\\nto the village. The strange caldera steam causes birth defects that are\\npleasing to the Frog God, and the young are born as troglodytes, but\\nwill not breed true reverting back to human in a few generations.\\nThe Zombie Float\\nThis island isn't so much an island as a collection of decomposing un -\\ndead crocodiles and other swamp life that has been built up into an\\nisland. It will be first encountered in this hex, but will then travel one\\nhex per day in a random direction (the direction is determined ran -\\ndomly each day), although obviously it will remain in the swamp and\\nwill avoid running aground. The floating zombie island can actually"], "metadata": [{"producer": "Adobe PDF Library 7.0", "creator": "Adobe InDesign CS2 (4.0)", "creationdate": "2011-06-10T11:24:01-04:00", "moddate": "2011-06-10T11:24:19-04:00", "trapped": "/False", "source": "dyson-logos-challenge-of-the-frog-idol.pdf", "total_pages": 23, "page": 11, "page_label": "12", "name": "dyson-logos-challenge-of-the-frog-idol.pdf", "created_by": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "file_id": "e144d21f-1c37-490c-866d-030fdb7ca5ff", "start_index": 865, "hash": "c211a00a07e709a943cc2ffdf530486bb80e2a55a60aaea6370b382770c0056d", "embedding_config": {"engine": "ollama", "model": "nomic-embed-text"}}, {"producer": "Adobe PDF Library 7.0", "creator": "Adobe InDesign CS2 (4.0)", "creationdate": "2011-06-10T11:24:01-04:00", "moddate": "2011-06-10T11:24:19-04:00", "trapped": "/False", "source": "dyson-logos-challenge-o