round, expertise, or strengths, I would need additional context to provide that information.", "model": "claude-3.7-sonnet", "modelName": "claude-3.7-sonnet", "modelIdx": 0, "timestamp": 1768416734, "statusHistory": [{"action": "queries_generated", "queries": ["Who is Justin notable figures with this name", "Justin common strengths and characteristics", "Justin famous people profiles"], "done": false}, {"action": "sources_retrieved", "count": 2, "done": true}], "sources": [{"source": {"type": "collection", "id": "adbeade6-cb53-42c9-88cc-adf0f39ec6df", "user_id": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "name": "Justin's Knowledge", "description": "This is information about Justin, and relevant research.", "meta": null, "access_control": {"read": {"group_ids": [], "user_ids": []}, "write": {"group_ids": [], "user_ids": []}}, "created_at": 1768337776, "updated_at": 1768337788, "user": {"id": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "name": "Pluto System", "role": "admin", "email": "system@pluto.local"}, "write_access": true, "status": "processed"}, "document": ["If IFMs are built independently, it is unlikely that strategy names, their descriptions will match identically and form a perfect comparison. In order for this comparison to be useful, strategy characteristics and their triggers need to be abstracted to comparable terminology. For example, if two strategies involve taking paper notes during a process, this characteristic (e.g. 'paper notes') would be used to compare strategies. The comparison would show which strategies from the domain that uses the specific strategy characteristic. If these strategy of using 'papers notes' was triggered by experience, this would also be noted in a table. The approach leaves practitioners with a summary of strategy characteristics and triggers that apply to either system and allows for a rich contrast for each task. If appropriate, the intersections and commonalities in strategy characteristics could be shown in a Venn diagram.", "Competency: A combination of knowledge, skills, and attributes; based on observable behaviors demonstrated across various job responsibilities (e.g. customer focus).\\nSkill: Measurable ability to perform or complete a specific task with proficiency. It can relate to an ability, a behavior, or a specific piece of knowledge.\\nUse an iterative process to proactively identify future skills!Download Identify Skills of the Future.\\nLearn more about adopting a skill-based mindset!Download What It Means to Become a Skills-Based Organization.\\nInput Output Scoreboard and Workbook From Step 2 Description of partners and competitors Materials Participants Whiteboard/Flip Charts Chief Marketing Officer\\nActivity 3.1 Prioritize your AI service competencies\\n1-3 hours\\nFamiliarize yourself with the Suggested Skill Sets slides in the AI Services framework.\\nOpen the Competency Workbook.\\nIdentify the top ten AI service competencies.", "Do you have Domain 5AI capabilities?\\nInfo-Tech Insight\\nWhen you develop internal capabilities, you create useful intellectual property that can be resold. The best service providers have internal capabilities first.\\nDomain 3Suggested Skill Sets"], "metadata": [{"source": "background_Ergonomics Manuscript - Final - Sept 26.docx", "name": "background_Ergonomics Manuscript - Final - Sept 26.docx", "created_by": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "file_id": "cd27234b-4d4b-4653-87d6-981bf18e7703", "start_index": 0, "hash": "4e4bd03cde537872863480da351490326983bb274b14642a48fa2edeea210185", "embedding_config": {"engine": "ollama", "model": "nomic-embed-text"}}, {"source": "01-Get-Ready-to-Deliver-AI-Services-Storyboard.pptx", "name": "01-Get-Ready-to-Deliver-AI-Services-Storyboard.pptx", "created_by": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "file_id": "db17bfb2-d6a2-4f17-92b8-335422bbe683", "start_index": 0, "hash": "092d092ae899bcb0ae6c80808d70dcefbe91d78dfe942e32c57ea33bce015e58", "embedding_config": {"engine": "ollama", "model": 