a workflow diagram for washing your dog. While the provided context contains information about patient flows and information workflows [1] and mentions workflow diagrams [2], it doesn't include specific Mermaid code examples for pet care.\\n\\nSince this isn't covered in the context, I can provide you with Mermaid code for a dog washing workflow based on my general knowledge:\\n\\n```mermaid\\nflowchart TD\\n    A[Start: Prepare for Dog Wash] --> B[Gather Supplies]\\n    B --> C[Fill Tub with Warm Water]\\n    C --> D[Get Dog]\\n    D --> E[Place Dog in Tub]\\n    E --> F[Wet Dog Thoroughly]\\n    F --> G[Apply Shampoo]\\n    G --> H[Scrub Dog]\\n    H --> I[Rinse Thoroughly]\\n    I --> J[Dry Dog with Towel]\\n    J --> K[Optional: Use Hair Dryer]\\n    K --> L[Brush Dog]\\n    L --> M[Reward Dog with Treat]\\n    M --> N[Clean Up Bath Area]\\n    N --> O[End: Dog Wash Complete]\\n```\\n\\nYou can copy this code and paste it into any Mermaid-compatible editor or viewer to generate the diagram.", "model": "claude-3.7-sonnet", "modelName": "claude-3.7-sonnet", "modelIdx": 0, "timestamp": 1768416829, "statusHistory": [{"action": "queries_generated", "queries": ["mermaid diagram syntax for workflow", "dog washing workflow steps", "how to create mermaid workflow diagrams"], "done": false}, {"action": "sources_retrieved", "count": 2, "done": true}], "sources": [{"source": {"type": "collection", "id": "adbeade6-cb53-42c9-88cc-adf0f39ec6df", "user_id": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "name": "Justin's Knowledge", "description": "This is information about Justin, and relevant research.", "meta": null, "access_control": {"read": {"group_ids": [], "user_ids": []}, "write": {"group_ids": [], "user_ids": []}}, "created_at": 1768337776, "updated_at": 1768337788, "user": {"id": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "name": "Pluto System", "role": "admin", "email": "system@pluto.local"}, "write_access": true, "status": "processed"}, "document": ["Workflows representing patient flows (Figure 1) and information workflows (Figure 2) were developed with SMEs to describe the generalized activities of the clinic and its clinicians. As generalized workflows, not all components of the workflow were necessarily 'activated' during each patient encounter but represented possible workflows during a visit. In the case of patient flows, most use-cases within the clinic (involving a combination of triage, assessment, treatment, care transfer and scheduling) were captured. In the case of information flows, most use-cases involving the EMR (involving a combination of summarization, sharing, updating and interpretation) were also captured. These workflows were later translated into the 'Generalized Function' layer of the abstraction hierarchy.\\nFigure 1 - Patient Flow Generalized Functions\\nFigure 2 - Information Flow Generalized Functions", "\\u2611 Internal Capability Checklist \\u2610 Do you have a process and predetermined criteria to align technology solutions with business problems? \\u2610 Do you have the capability to create detailed workflow diagrams that represent both current and future states of business processes? \\u2610 Can you build a transition plan to go from old workflows to new workflows after a detailed analysis? \\u2610 Do you have a process to ensure diagrams effectively communicate the insights gathered from stakeholders? \\u2610 Do you have a repeatable process to assess, document, and update business processes? \\u2610 Do you use multiple types of research to assess current and future process states? \\u2610 How do you conduct market analyses to identify vendor offers that are best aligned with your application needs? \\u2610 Do you have specific strategies to engage stakeholders during a solution selection process? \\u2610 Do you have a standard process or tool to translate business requirements into technical specifications? \\u2610 Are you able to describe", "How do you align technical capabilities with a specific business need?\\nCan you give an example of how you translate business needs into technical specifications for an AI solution?\\nHow do you approach creating workflow diagrams for existing processes and proposed AI augmentation?\\nWhat methods do you use to ensure that the selected AI solution aligns with both current and future business processes?\\nHow do you approach the issue of buy vs. build when considering AI technology?\\nDomain 3Service Product Opportunities\\nBUY VS. BUILD ANALYSIS\\nADVISORY SERVICE\\nHelp organizations assess and select the most suitable AI solutions for their specific business need. Conduct market analyses, evaluate AI technologies, and recommend solutions that align with workflow needs and program objectives.\\nREQUIREMENTS ALIGNMENT SERVICES\\nMANAGED SERVICE"], "metadata": [{"source": "background_JHF 2016 - Modeling the Treatment of Patients - Final.docx", "name": "background_JHF 2016 - Modeling the Treatment of Patients - Final.docx", "created_by": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "file_id": "f2adc271-6177-44a2-a173-ade8713b2323", "start_index": 0, "hash": "437b1676e9a7323cf386390cc4e48440642c5eb19e52ec1c1a012072575f0c24", "embedding_config": {"engine": "ollama", "model": "nomic-embed-text"}}, {"source": "01-Get-Ready-to-Deliver-AI-Services-Storyboard.pptx", "name": "01-Get-Ready-to-Deliver-AI-Services-Storyboard.pptx", "created_by": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "file_id": "db17bfb2-d6a2-4f17-92b8-335422bbe683", "start_index": 0, "hash": "092d092ae899bcb0ae6c80808d70dcefbe91d78dfe942e32c57ea33bce015e58", "embedding_config": {"engine": "ollama", "model": "nomic-embed-text"}}, {"source": "01-Get-Ready-to-Deliver-AI-Services-Storyboard.pptx", "name": "01-Get-Ready-to-Deliver-AI-Services-Storyboard.pptx", "created_by": "e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9", "file_id": "db17bfb2-d6a2-4f17-92b8-335422bbe683", "start_index": 0, "hash": "092d092ae899bcb0ae6c80808d70dcefbe91d78dfe942e32c57ea33bce015e58", "embedding_config": {"