ctitioner to highlight similarities and differences between the work domains (St-Maurice & Burns, 2015). This Venn diagram should be accompanied by a comparison table that discusses and comments on each noted difference.", "3.6 Work Competency Analyses Comparisons\\nWhen comparing WCA, the first step is to create detailed SRK taxonomies for each control task. For each task under study, the task's skill-based, rule-based and knowledge-based behaviours are identified and described. Once complete, the comparison of each SRK taxonomy is shown for information processing step. In a table format, behaviours are aligned to which elements of the SRK taxonomies are unique and overlap. Since it is unlikely that text descriptions in the SRK match exactly verbatim between two independently generated models all behaviours need to be summarized and abstracted before attempting to draw comparisons.", "Leverage Generative AI to Create Unique Visuals for Presentations\\nAudience\\nGeneral\\nOverview\\nLearn to communicate your ideas using Generative AI image generation and start creating memorable visuals for your presentations today! See how to draw your thoughts, describe your vision, roll the dice and, eventually, accept the output of your prompts. Join to see the iterative development of a comic, a unique example of data drift and learn how to add this capability to your presentation toolkit.\\nType\\nLightning Talk\\nLength\\n5 minutes (can be expanded!)\\nPresentation Title\\nDesign With the Human-Tech Ladder\\nAudience\\nGeneral\\nOverview\\nThis session reviews the thought model presented in the \\"Wireframe Your Generative AI Solution Design\\" blueprint. The model decomposes problems and requirements according to a human-tech ladder, which is helpful in the development of AI solutions.\\nType\\nLightning Talk\\nLength\\n5 minutes (can be expanded!)\\nPresentation Title"], "metadata": [{"source": "background_Ergonomics Manuscript - Final - Sept 26.docx", "name": "background_