105e8074-7119-4d32-a79c-b05295abe1d1	e92fa032-845e-4ce9-ad71-3810ca14f7a9	2022 - Justin St-Maurice BIO.docx	{"name": "2022 - Justin St-Maurice BIO.docx", "content_type": "application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document", "size": 134343, "data": {"knowledge_id": "adbeade6-cb53-42c9-88cc-adf0f39ec6df"}, "collection_name": "adbeade6-cb53-42c9-88cc-adf0f39ec6df"}	1768337833	befcddcd175800b3cfc8976bc2e7c01feb9dd2cd1819bb271eea155fd525c5fa	{"status": "completed", "content": "Principal Research Director\\n\\nTechnology Services Provider Industry\\n\\nInfo-Tech Research Group\\n\\nPrincipal Research Director\\n\\nTechnology Services Provider Industry\\n\\nInfo-Tech Research Group\\n\\nDr. Justin St-Maurice\\n\\nDr. Justin St-Maurice \\n\\n\\n\\nDr. Justin St-Maurice is a Principal Research Director at Info-Tech Research Group. He specializes in helping Technology Service Providers modernize service delivery models with business reference architectures, industry insights and systems thinking. With a focus on aligning technology innovation with business goals, Justin guides clients by leveraging unique industry models to uncover new opportunities for commodity service offers. He also supports cloud engineering teams as a technical counselor, leveraging his expertise in solution architecture, development, and data analytics to build modern systems.\\n\\n\\n\\nThroughout his career, Justin has embraced a generalist approach, working across various industries as a technology leader. His background includes significant contributions to health informatics and systems design, earning him multiple industry awards, including an Industrial Partnership Award from the Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council of Canada. His broad expertise allows him to maintain a big-picture perspective, ensuring that technology solutions are both effective and user-centric.\\n\\n\\n\\nJustin's passion for technology is matched by his commitment to education and community service. He spent eight years in the classroom, earning a prestigious teaching award for his contributions. As a certified coach, he brings a unique perspective to his technical counseling portfolio while also volunteering with Up With Women, an organization dedicated to helping homeless and at-risk women rebuild their lives. He plays cello with the Cambridge Symphony Orchestra and looses regularly in Guelph's least-competitive curling league."}	1768337834	/app/backend/data/uploads/105e8074-7119-4d32-a79c-b05295abe1d1_2022 - Justin St-Maurice BIO.docx	null
