iness.\\n\\nNot critical to the business, where failure would have a disproportionate negative impact business viability. \\n\\nRecognize Strategic Value\\n\\nIdentify clients where successful implementation would lead to significant strategic benefits, such as:\\n\\nEntry into new markets or industries.\\n\\nEnhancement of key capabilities that advance long-term business goals.\\n\\nAbility to grow key business. metrics, such as Net Promoter Scores\\n\\nStrategic\\n\\nPartner\\n\\n\\n\\nInput Output List of current customers, with relevant metadata. AI Services Client Personas Materials Participants Whiteboard/Flip Charts Chief Marketing Officer\\n\\nActivity 1.1 Develop Your Client Personas\\n\\n1 hour\\n\\nDescribe criteria for launching AI Services to an existing customer.\\n\\nWhat level of AI maturity does your ideal AI Services customer have? What type of AI user are you looking to serve?\\n\\nWhat type of relationship maturity do you have with your ideal AI Services customer? How will you position your services?\\n\\nWhat is your risk tolerance for offering AI Services to an existing customer? What do you consider strategically valuable?\\n\\nCreate customer personas.\\n\\nSelect three or four customers to turn into personas. Write three or four sentences for each persona and record it in the workbook.\\n\\nFor each persona, use the workbook to apply your criteria from step 1 to describe your existing customer persona:\\n\\nDescribe this persona's AI maturity.\\n\\nDescribe your relationship maturity with this persona.\\n\\nDescribe the business risks associated with this persona.\\n\\nDescribe the strategic opportunities associated with this persona.\\n\\nDownload the AI Service Opportunity Workbook\\n\\nInfo-Tech Research Group   |   26\\n\\n\\n\\nUnderstand the target of your services by using a service abstraction ladder\\n\\nWhy?Human Focus\\n\\nHow?Technology Focus\\n\\nKnow the noun!Be intentional about the target of your AI service offering. \\n\\nOr