udit data policies, metadata requirements, and data management processes. Ensure compliance with data protection regulations.\\n\\nDATA INTEGRATION AS A SERVICE\\n\\nProvide organizations with a platform for integrating and accessing data, testing data models, and preparing models for AI models. Provide data integration tools, data pipelines, and APIs to enable seamless data integration from disparate sources into useful AI-centric data structures.\\n\\nCLOUD SERVICE\\n\\nDomain 5Knowledge\\n\\nData\\n\\nGovernance\\n\\nData LifecycleManagement\\n\\nDataIntegration\\n\\nData Quality\\n\\nManagement\\n\\nDataArchitecture\\n\\nLeverage programs to manage data quality and integrity. Implement controls to correct errors, maintain consistency, and enforce quality.\\n\\nEstablish data governance frameworks. Define data policies, roles, and responsibilities. Implement stewardship, compliance, and accountability.\\n\\nCreate data models that support custom analytics. Define data structures, relationships, and constraints to optimize data storage and retrieval.\\n\\nManage the lifecycle of data from creation and storage to archiving and deletion. Ensure data remains accurate and useful over time.\\n\\nIntegrate data from disparate sources. Design and implement integration processes, data mapping strategies, and interoperable data architectures. \\n\\n\\n\\nDomain 5Organizational Self-Assessment\\n\\n\\u2611 Internal Capability Checklist \\u2610 Do you have an operational data pipeline that can quickly incorporate data from new sources? \\u2610 Do you have a process to measure and improve data quality? \\u2610 Do you have a process to assign metadata to data sources? \\u2610 Do you have a mature data governance program within your organization? \\u2610 Do you have an information management team? \\u2610 Do you have a process to design and test data structures that are optimized for the specific requirements of an AI algorithm? \\u2610 Do you have guiding principles to help yo