ve specific criteria that influence the choice between vector, NoSQL, and SQL databases? \\u2610 Do you have documented guidelines to follow for coding AI solutions to ensure high-quality and maintainable code? \\u2610 Do you have expertise to systematically manage the deployment of AI solutions while minimizing disruptions to legacy systems? \\u2610 Do you have rollback policies and an operational CI/CD pipeline to minimize impacts on production systems? \\u2610 Do you incorporate privacy by design philosophies into your implementation of technology solutions? \\u2610 Do you incorporate security by default and data protection measures into the development and deployment of AI solutions? \\u2610 How do you utilize CI/CD practices in the development and deployment of AI solutions? \\u2610 Do you have an integration platform, pattern, or partner to successfully connect external systems? \\u2610 Do you have policies requiring regular code reviews and professional development for programmers? \\u2610 Do you have change management strategies to support the integration of AI and legacy technologies? \\u2610 Do you have a process to assess compliance with ethical considerations into your system design?\\n\\nDo you have Domain 6AI capabilities?\\n\\nInfo-Tech Insight\\n\\nWhen you develop internal capabilities, you create useful intellectual property that can be resold. The best service providers have internal capabilities first. \\n\\n\\n\\nDomain 6Suggested Skill Sets (System Design)\\n\\nCompetency Description of Competency Source Application of technical solutions Designing, implementing, and delivering effective and efficient solutions to meet expectations. This involves identifying the best possible solutions based on the data and requirements available and providing clear and relevant guidance to technical and nontechnical audiences. Info-Tech's AI Competency Library Software design Specifying and designing software to meet defined requirements by following agreed design standards and principles. SFIA Competency Library Solution architecture Developing and communicating a multidimensional solution architecture to deliver agreed business outcomes. SFIA Competency Library Systems design Designing systems to meet specified requirements and agreed systems architectures. SFIA Competency Library Systems integration and build Planning, implementing, and controlling activities to synthesize system components to create operational systems, products, or services. SFIA Competency Library\\n\\nNeed a deeper dive on AI competencies and skills?Download (Re)Calibrate Your IT Workforce for AI.\\n\\n\\n\\nDomain 6Suggested Skill Sets (System Development)\\n\\nCompetency Description of Competency Source Application of technical solutions Designing, implementing, and delivering effective and efficient solutions to meet expectations. This involves identifying the best possible solutions based on the data and requirements available and providing clear and relevant guidance to technical and nontechnical audiences. Info-Tech's AI Competency Library Systems and Establishing and deploying an environment for developing, continually improving, and securely operating software and systems products and services. SFIA Competency Library Programming & software development Developing software components to deliver value to stakeholders. SFIA Competency Library Systems development management Planning, estimating, and executing systems development work to time, budget, and quality targets. SFIA Competency Library Real-time/embedded systems development Designing and developing reliable real-time software typically within embedded systems. SFIA Competency Library\\n\\nNeed a deeper dive on AI competencies?Download (Re)Calibrate Your IT Workforce for AI.\\n\\n\\n\\nDomain 6Cindy Pawford Pet Company (Part 6)\\n\\nCould you meet Cindy's service needs?\\n\\nClient Profile\\n\\nAI Service Needs\\n\\nCan you \\u2026 \\n\\nThe Cindy Pawford Pet Company (CPPC) is an inter