ms for vulnerabilities and security threats? \\u2610 Do you use data center infrastructure management (DCIM) tools and practices to optimize physical infrastructure? \\u2610 Do you leverage virtualization and container technologies (VMware, Docker, and Kubernetes) to improve resource utilization?\\n\\nDo you have Domain 1AI capabilities?\\n\\nInfo-Tech Insight\\n\\nWhen you develop internal capabilities, you create useful intellectual property that can be resold. The best service providers have internal capabilities first. \\n\\n\\n\\nDomain 7Suggested Skill Sets\\n\\nSkill Description of Skill Source AI systems scaling The ability to scale AI capabilities, manage large-scale AI projects, and understand the infrastructure/security needed for AI applications. Info-Tech's AI Competency Library Release and deployment Applying the processes, systems, and functions required to make new and changed services and features available for use. SFIA Competency Library IT Deploying, configuring, and operating IT Infrastructure. SFIA Competency Library Audit Delivering independent, risk-based assessments of the effectiveness of processes, the controls, and the compliance environment of an organization. SFIA Competency Library Hardware Specifying a hardware design model for a defined system architecture. SFIA Competency Library\\n\\nNeed a deeper dive on AI competencies and skills?Download (Re)Calibrate Your IT Workforce for AI.\\n\\n\\n\\nDomain 7Cindy Pawford Pet Company (Part 7)\\n\\nCould you meet Cindy's service needs?\\n\\nClient Profile\\n\\nAI Service Needs\\n\\nCan you \\u2026\\n\\nThe Cindy Pawford Pet Company (CPPC) is an international veterinary clinic franchiser that offers veterinary services as a service (VaaS). Customers pay membership fees to access online veterinary consults and can be referred to a franchised clinic for follow-up without limit. Members get preferred rates from partners on food, toys, and spa services. CPPC also sells a mutual pet insurance product. \\n\\nCindy, the CTO, has successfully launched a popular preventative health feature for pets worldwide. Unfortunately, energy costs have risen dramatically, and the cost of commercial model licensing has stopped making business sense. \\n\\nCindy needs to optimize costs or will need to remove the feature from the product. \\n\\nFinOps Cost Optimization: Cindy wants to monitor, benchmark, and minimize the LLM operating costs. She is open to hosting servers in a data center instead of leveraging the cloud, if this provided a meaningful ROI. \\n\\nLLM Optimization: Cindy wants to understand how to reduce costs by deploying a small, purpose-specific LLM that is trained specifically to provide preventative healthcare plans for pets. She wants a customized LLM trained from the ground up and optimized to operate reliably on ten GB of memory. \\n\\nConfigure FinOps to provide visibility into computer costs associated with AI technologies?\\n\\nOptimize overall solution performance to minimize total costs?\\n\\nCompare on-premises hosting against cloud hosting costs for AI technology?\\n\\nMinimize the size of a model's memory requirements and optimize systems to run on non-GPU configurations?\\n\\nOptimize compilers, manage driver updates, and leverage third-party libraries?\\n\\nManage clusters to ensure high availability?\\n\\nLearn more by visiting 11 Proven Strategies to Reduce Large Language Model (LLM) Costs\\n\\n\\n\\nInput Output Client Profiles From Step 1 Service Capability Score Materials Participants Whiteboard/Flip Charts Chief Technology Officer\\n\\nActivity 2.7 Assess your systems optimization service capabilities \\n\\n1-3 hours\\n\\nSelect Systems Optimization as the AI service domain and enter your answers in the table.\\n\\n\\u200fTalent Assessment Questions: Rate your current teams' ability to successfully answer each question in an interview scenario, on a scale from 1 (unsatisfactory) to 5 (exemplary).\\n\\n\\u200fBusiness Model Assessment Quest