rvice domain to align your hiring strategies and professional development planning with future service opportunities.\\n\\nCompetency: A combination of knowledge, skills, and attributes; based on observable behaviors demonstrated across various job responsibilities (e.g. customer focus).\\n\\nSkill: Measurable ability to perform or complete a specific task with proficiency. It can relate to an ability, a behavior, or a specific piece of knowledge. \\n\\nUse an iterative process to proactively identify future skills!Download Identify Skills of the Future.\\n\\nLearn more about adopting a skill-based mindset!Download What It Means to Become a Skills-Based Organization.\\n\\n\\n\\nInput Output Scoreboard and Workbook From Step 2 Description of partners and competitors Materials Participants Whiteboard/Flip Charts Chief Marketing Officer\\n\\nActivity 3.1 Prioritize your AI service competencies\\n\\n1-3 hours\\n\\n\\u200fFamiliarize yourself with the Suggested Skill Sets slides in the AI Services framework.\\n\\n\\u200fOpen the Competency Workbook.\\n\\nIdentify the top ten AI service competencies.\\n\\nSelect competencies that align with your business model, market, and strategy.\\n\\n\\u200fComplete the ranking for each of your AI service domains.\\n\\nDownload the AI Service Competency Workbook\\n\\nInfo-Tech Research Group   |   80\\n\\n\\n\\nAn AI service domain is part of a larger ecosystem\\n\\nCompetitors operate in common domains, and partners operate elsewhere to form a larger ecosystem.\\n\\nPartners\\n\\nYou and your competitors(illustrative example)\\n\\nInfo-Tech Insight\\n\\nProviders in the ecosystem are unlikely to break this out as cleanly as shown here because they will likely span multiple domains. Finding the right partner is also about aligning on ethical frameworks, specialization, industry, and maturity.\\n\\nPartners\\n\\n\\n\\nBe strategic about competencies and recruitment: Strategically invest in competitive skill sets while trusting your par