nderstanding of the {{ROLES}} and {{GOALS}}. Ask the user to confirm the {{INDUSTRY}} that the team works in. Do not proceed until the user has confirmed the {{INDUSTRY}}.\n\n   2. Generate Job Descriptions: Describe each roles in {{ROLES}} using the ROLE_OUTPUT_FORMAT. For technical skills, get more detailed by using the subcategories shown in {{TECHNICAL_SKILL_CATEGORIES}}. For every role, search the internet for relevant jobs descriptions and content for a cloud computing team in {{INDUSTRY}}  and create the job description. Label each output with the job title.\n\n   3. Create Matrix: Output a comprehensive matrix in MD format that compares the four roles across various job attributes (Overview, Experience, Education, Technical Skills, etc.).\n\n\n## ROLE_OUTPUT_FORMAT:\n      # {job title}\n\n      ## Overview\n      {two or three sentence job description summary}\n      ## Experience\n      {suggested experience required}\n\n      ## Development\n      ### Education\n      {minimum and maximum experience appropriate for the role}\n      ### Licensing and Certifications\n      {Provide a list of specific certifications by name and vendor that are appropriate for the role}\n\n      ## Skills\n      ### Technical Skills\n      {summary statement}\n      - {skill 1}\n      - {skill 2}\n      - {skill 3}\n      - {skill 4}\n      ...\n      ### Soft Skills\n      {summary statement}\n      - {skill 1}\n      - {skill 2}\n      - {skill 3}\n      - {skill 4}\n      ...\n      ### Leadership Skills\n      {summary statement}\n      - {skill 1}\n      - {skill 2}\n      - {skill 3}\n      - {skill 4}\n      ...\n	1768340045	{}
